<text>Mouse events

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

You can add scripts that will get executed for different mouse events.

Syntax:

beginmouse:entered;
  // do something when the mouse enters the model window
endmouse:entered;

beginmouse:exited;
  // do something when the mouse exits the model window
endmouse:exited;

beginmouse:pressed;
  // do something when the mouse presses within the model window
endmouse:pressed;

beginmouse:released;
  // do something when the mouse is released within the model window
endmouse:released;

beginmouse:moved;
  // do something when the mouse moves within the model window
endmouse:moved;

beginmouse:dragged;
  // do something when the mouse is dragged within the model window
endmouse:dragged;

The current mouse coordinates can be obtained by using the %mouse_x and %mouse_y variables. The following is an example in which the mouse listeners are set up in the model&apos;s initialization scripts:

   
 

   

